what does my dream mean i had a dream last night were my teeth fell out in crushed up pieces i was spitting it out which scared me what does it mean i have had dreams before where my teeth fall out but usually they fall out whole and one at a time so why now do i dreams my teeth are broken into tiny pieces dreams that your teeth are falling out are the most common dreams common dream scenarios include having your teeth crumbling in your hands or your teeth falling out one by one with just a light tap such dreams are not only horrifying and shocking but often leaves the dreamer with a lasting image of the dream so what does it mean one theory is that dreams about your teeth reflect your anxiety about your appearance and how others perceive you sadly we live in a world where good looks are valued highly and your teeth play an important role in conveying that image teeth are used in the game of flirtations whether it be a dazzling and gleaming smile or affectionate necking these dreams may stem from a fear of your sexual impotence or the consequences of getting old teeth are an important feature of our attractiveness and presentation to others everybody worries about how they appear to others caring about our appearance is natural and healthy another rationalization for these falling teeth dream may be rooted in your fear of being embarrassed or making a fool of yourself in some specific situation these dreams are an over exaggeration of your worries and anxiety teeth are used to bite tear chew and gnaw in this regard teeth represent power and the loss of teeth in your dream may be from a sense of powerlessness are you lacking power in some current situation perhaps you are having difficulties expressing yourself or getting your point across you feel frustrated when your voice is not being heard you may be experiencing feelings of inferiority and a lack of self confidence in some situation or relationship in your life this dream is an indication that you need to be more assertive and believe in the value of your own opinion in the latest research it has been shown that women in menopause have frequent dreams about teeth this may be related to getting older and or feeling unattractive and less feminine traditionally it was thought that dreaming that you did not have teeth represent malnutrition which may be applicable to some dreamers Narcissism Dog Physical attractiveness Karen Horney Infantilism Baldness Carl Jung Homophobia Panic attack Procrastination Psychoanalysis Tooth Transsexuality Clinical depression Tonality Psychology of religion Stuttering Sigmund Freud Modernism Sleep Sexual orientation Philosophical skepticism Borderline personality disorder Methamphetamine Asperger syndrome Social rule Urinary incontinence Theodicy Second language acquisition Mad scientist Child sexuality Simone Weil Breastfeeding Anorexia nervosa Cocaine Hamster Yoga Sutras of Patanjali The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Gender role Prostate cancer Anger management Theory of conduct Leaf Drill bit Kim Possible Fathers' rights Characters in the Smurfs Milton H. Erickson Expert system Obsessive-compulsive disorder Music Autism Gender-neutral language Jon Secada Germaine Greer W.I.T.C.H. Cultural relativism Bish__jo game Human Dissociative identity disorder Domestic violence Internet troll Utilitarianism Objectivist philosophy Zoophilia The Descent of Man, and Selection in Relation to Sex Eyes Wide Shut Strategic management Menstrual cycle Kurt Angle Maison Ikkoku Ethics Traumatic brain injury Stroke Mojave people Anxiety Phaedo Humphrey Bogart Psychosis Blade Runner Scenes from a Memory A Course In Miracles Philosophy of language Human height The Amber Spyglass Friedrich Nietzsche Tai Chi Chuan The Smoking Room Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Dream Theater Harem anime Michel Henry 